---
title: Grilled Coley with Fennel Remoulade and Bulgur Salad
description: Coley is a great tasting white fish with a similar meaty texture to cod making it a versatile ingredient to use in fresh recipes like this one. Its flaky texture works brilliantly with the crunchy fennel remoulade which is packed with fibre, Vitamin C and potassium, and the nutty bulgar wheat and kale mix. In order to obtain the nutrients from dark leafy kale, and to save time washing up, we’ve steamed it in the same pan as the bulgar wheat and fluffed it up with salt and pepper for a delicious side.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/grilled-coley-34e2a503-1d75f1e6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/grilled-coley-5c127284e3f3396b2d6623d2-db2f574e.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/grilled-coley-5c127284e3f3396b2d6623d2
cuisine: British
nutrition:
  calories: 341 kcal
